{"id":"254211616_Wasserstein_geometry_of_Gaussian_measures","abstract":"This paper concerns the Riemannian/Alexandrov geometry of\nGaussian measures, from the view point of the $L^{2}$-Wasserstein\ngeometry. The space of Gaussian measures is of finite dimension,\nwhich allows to write down the explicit Riemannian metric \nwhich in turn induces the $L^{2}$-Wasserstein distance. Moreover,\nits completion as a metric space provides a complete picture\nof the singular behavior of the $L^{2}$-Wasserstein geometry.\nIn particular, the singular set is stratified according to\nthe dimension of the support of the Gaussian measures, providing\nan explicit nontrivial example of Alexandrov space with extremal\nsets.","authors":["Asuka Takatsu"],"meta":["December 2011OSAKA JOURNAL OF MATHEMATICS 48(2011)"],"references":["228349272_Ricci_flow_entropy_and_optimal_transportation","225489419_On_the_geometry_of_metric_measure_spaces_I","225176242_Polar_factorization_of_maps_on_Riemannian_manifolds","222493049_A_Convexity_Principle_for_Interacting_Gases","284881087_Elements_of_Morse_theory_on_Aleksandrov_spaces","284024097_A_D_Aleksandrov_spaces_with_curvatures_bounded_below","271512781_Probability_and_Measure","265333347_Extremal_subsets_in_Aleksandrov_spaces_and_the_generalized_Liberman_theorem","255592560_L-optimal_transportation_for_Ricci_flow","247867825_The_entropy_formula_for_Ricci_flow_and_its_geometric_applications_preprint","247040370_On_the_geometry_of_metric_measure_spaces_II","246337770_Gradient_Flows_in_Metric_Spaces_and_in_the_Space_of_Probability_Measures","244954851_AD_Alexandrov_spaces_with_curvature_bounded_below","242324408_Grundlehren_der_mathematischen_wissenschaften_278","239964497_Elements_of_Morse_theory_on_Aleksandrov_spaces","239230352_Topics_in_Optimal_Transportation_Theory","235409844_Differential-Geometrical_Methods_in_Statistics","228802706_A_Course_in_Metric_Geometry","227632352_Polar_Factorization_and_Monotone_Rearrangement_of_Vector-Valued_Functions",